<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Zero on 12-07-2000 02:29 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Okay, what we have is a way to get the key from the win32 box but that method of getting the key is detectable.  Now, Verant promised not to use the method in which they can detect our method of getting the key ever.
Write a program with a few functions, one would be to allow all but flagged programs to access memory outside their block.  The next function is to monitor wether a program is attempting to access memory outside it's block.  Next is to log any and all attempts made to access memory outside flagged programs blocks.  Next is to stop flagged programs from calling on any programs on functions other than those that are authorized.
Now, as far as I can tell this is doable by a skilled win32 programmer (I'm not one, hell I'm not even skilled).  If it isn't possible to deny a program access to any memory other than it's own I know it is the monitor the programs actions and halt it if it tries to...  Worst case scenario we only come up with a program that monitors what parts of memory another program tries to access.
Now, we have a way to know if Verant is trying to break their word.  But they can still ban us, even if they do break their word our accounts are still banned.
So we know when they access our information, but we can't keep them from accessing it.  Make the program that logs the information public, email lum, castersrealm, eqvault, everlore.  All those popular sites...  The general player populace will now know for sure if Verant is checking out their information, the general player populace will download a program that has nothing do with EQ except a player made it.  The program is running on comps of people who are not using ShowEQ, Verant can't scan the memory, they have no grounds to ban, we can do whatever we want in the background (even implement a windows SEQ).

Any reasons why I'm an idiot and this isn't possible?  I know PR enough to know that Verant wont have the balls to do anything if a program like this becomes public and known to regular EQ users.  Ideally the ratio of SEQ users to non-SEQ users will be 10:1 so for every SEQ user banned they also get 10 who aren't SEQ users.

If I'm an idiot and there's no way this will work feel free to say so, just trying to contribute to a wonderful community  <IMG SRC="http://hackersquest.gomp.ch/ubb/smile.gif"></TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
